The paper deals with the problem of finding maximum-area rectangles contained in a polygon in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. The paper presents algorithms for both simple polygons and convex polygons, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of space complexity in the algorithm suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem of finding maximum-area rectangles is related to the problem of finding the largest empty rectangle, which is a well-studied problem in computational geometry and could place the paper in cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
